Intuition
When i looke dat this problem i realized it is a sliding window problem with fixed window size , now my inofrmation is i need to see if permutation of s1 is in s2 so for that i realized if i calaculate freq map of s1 and For each window, I maintain its frequency map and compare it with s1’s frequency. If they match at any point, I return true. , otherwise keep sliding if high reaches out of s2 return false.

Approach
edge condition if len(s1) > len(s2)
return false
calculate freq map of s1
calcualte freq map of first window
compare freq map of first window and s1 if both equal return true
else slide window

sliding the window , add one element in window , add it into freq map of window , remove the freq of low from window freq map , increase low
check condition if freq map of window == freq map of s1 ,return true

else return false

Complexity
Time complexity:
O(n)
Space complexity:
O(1)
Code
class Solution:
    def checkInclusion(self, s1: str, s2: str) -> bool:
        if len(s1) > len(s2):
            return False
        freqs1 = {}
        for ch in range(len(s1)):
            freqs1[s1[ch]] = freqs1.get(s1[ch] ,0) + 1

        low = 0

        window_freq = {}
        for i in range(len(s1)):
            window_freq[s2[i]] = window_freq.get(s2[i], 0) + 1

        if window_freq == freqs1:
            return True
        
        for high in range(len(s1) , len(s2)):
        
            window_freq[s2[high]] = window_freq.get(s2[high] , 0) + 1
            window_freq[s2[low]] -= 1
            if window_freq[s2[low]] == 0:
                del window_freq[s2[low]]
            low +=1
            if window_freq == freqs1:
                return True
            
        return False
